query: How will The IJCAI 2023 handle submissions of research project proposals in the "Multi-Year Track on AI and Social Good" special track?
output: The IJCAI 2023 will invite submissions of research project proposals in the "Multi-Year Track on AI and Social Good" special track. These proposals are expected to go beyond research objectives and establish collaborative work lines between NGOs, academic research, and governmental agencies. Submissions can vary from incipient project ideas to projects already under development, provided they are based on in-the-field know-how, have a multi-lateral teamwork approach, and have a clear implementation plan for real-world impact on the UN SDGs and LNOB principle.

query: What is the primary focus of the "Multi-Year Track on AI and Social Good" special track at IJCAI 2023?
output: The primary focus of the "Multi-Year Track on AI and Social Good" special track at IJCAI 2023 is to encourage the application of AI to solve current global and local challenges, work towards the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) and the Leave No One Behind (LNOB) principle, and strengthen the civil society-science-policy interface. It supports interdisciplinary research, including computer, social and natural sciences, as well as collaborations with NGOs, community organizations, and government agencies. They particularly appreciate submissions dealing with real-world challenges and collaborations with stakeholders who have first-hand knowledge of the topic, especially local and regional African NGOs.

query: What are the requirements for submitting research papers to the "AI The Arts And Creativity" special track?
output: The research papers for the "AI The Arts And Creativity" special track must be submitted in the same format and general instructions as for the main conference. There will be no summary reject phase and no rebuttal. It is not required to upload extra files for previously rejected papers. The submissions must meet all the Submission Requirements mentioned in the general instructions. In particular, they must be anonymous and expected to satisfy the highest scientific standards as submissions to the main track of IJCAI 2023. Double submissions to the special track and main conference are not allowed. Authors can submit up to 50MB of supplementary material in PDF or ZIP format, such as appendices, artifacts, data, or source code. This material should directly support the submission content and must be anonymized.
